other Down\n| note7          = live at Milton Keynes '82\n| title8         = Somebody to Love\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nInformation is based on Queen's Complete Works<ref name=\"Purvis\">{{cite book|last=Purvis|first=George|title=Queen: Complete Works (Revised & Updated)|publisher=Titan Books|date=October 2018|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z9xkDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT98&lpg=PT98&dq=queen+tie+your+mother+down+harmonium+by+brian+may&source=bl&ots=3x7C_y9dkX&sig=ACfU3U3XTNGS97rU1PE1wH6TZL0zRxTFoA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjiy9HC_qLhAhVDMd8KHUNHDhUQ6AEwCnoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=queen%20tie%20your%20mother%20down%20harmonium%20by%20brian%20may&f=false}}</ref> and on the album's Liner Notes<ref>Queen.  \"A Day at the Races\" (Album Notes).  EMI.   1976.</ref><br>Track numbering refers to CD and digital releases of the album.\n\n'''Queen'''\n*[[Freddie Mercury]] \u2013 [[lead vocalist|lead vocals]] {{small|(1, 2, 4\u20138, 10)}}, [[backing vocalist|backing vocals]] {{small|(all but 9)}}, [[Chorus effect|gospel choir vocals]] {{small|(6)}}, [[piano]] {{small|(2, 4\u20136, 8)}}\n*[[Brian May]] \u2013 [[electric guitar]] {{small|(all tracks)}}, [[slide guitar]] {{small|(1, 9)}}, [[Orchestration|guitar orchestration]] {{small|(4)}}, [[harmonium]] {{small|(1, 10)}}, piano {{small|(10)}}, backing vocals {{small|(1, 3\u20138, 10)}}, gospel choir vocals {{small|(6)}}, lead vocals {{small|(3)}}\n*[[Roger Taylor (Queen drummer)|Roger Taylor]] \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]] {{small|(all but 2)}}, [[percussion instrument|percussion]] {{small|(1, 2, 8, 10)}}, [[timpani]] {{small|(9)}}, [[Rhythm guitar|rhythm electric guitar]] {{small|(9)}}, backing vocals {{small|(all but 2)}}, gospel choir vocals {{small|(6)}}, lead vocals {{small|(9)}}\n*[[John Deacon]] \u2013 [[bass guitar]] {{small|(all tracks)}}, [[acoustic guitar]] {{small|(5)}}\n\n'''Additional personnel'''\n*[[Mike Stone (record producer)|Mike Stone]] \u2013 additional background vocals {{small|(8)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==